latestPosts.caption:
Sometimes the most difficult decisions are the easiest ones to take. For me, this decision was to quit my much-loved VC job to start my own entrepreneurial journey. COVID-19 was an unusual time for all. There were two emotions that kept the world going – empathy and compassion. I have understood the meaning of these two words through the years from these women. Whether it is in their selflessness in dedicating themselves to their families or the unique perspective they add in a room full of well-suited men. 
Over the last 4 years, the more I learnt, the more I felt like a part of me was missing. After spending nights introspecting, days drawing out white boards – the answer was just lying in the women around me and the woman in me. Those who know me know how much I value self-care and self-love. I have never shied away from saying I need my space and I need my time. While my mother has ensured that I have that right, it was much later I realized that neither does she has the time and probably nor the will anymore to practise the same. 
Self-care is a privilege! Unfortunate but true. And that has got to change. My hope and my vision is simple – first, self-care should be a right and I will do my part by offering products that are affordable, accessible and the absolute best, and second, empathy will be the driving force of each of my endeavours through a community of empowered women who will help perpetuate this message further.
Listening, Understanding and Executing are the hallmarks that I will abide by and I hope a lot of you will join me in this vision and make this journey beautiful. 
Today I write this as an ode to every woman who has inspired me in ways known and unknown to take the most pivotal decision of my life. 
It is time for us to voice what we need and support each other in making that voice louder. 

It is our time! Let us redefine being perfect – let’s be bold, let’s be kind and let’s be authentic! 
Happy Women’s Day!
8.03.2021
Romita 
A special shoutout to @pooja_and_norah . I haven’t met you two but the inspiration the you have been over the last few months is indescribable.
